Four people died on Saturday in an accident along the Kericho-Nakuru highway involving two vehicles.
The road accident occurred at Ringa near Kedowa trading centre in Kipkelion East, Kericho County at around midday.
"A Toyota probox vehicle headed to Kericho town collided head-on with a Nissan Xtrail travelling towards Nakuru leading to the fatalities,” said Mr Silas Gichunge, the Kericho County Police Commander.



