According to the police, the victims were all in the probox vehicle while the occupants of the Nissan Xtrail are said to have escaped without injuries.
"I am calling on motor vehicle owners to be careful while on the road. Passengers should also report motorists who break traffic rules by speeding and overloading,” said Mr Gichunge on phone.
The mangled wreckage of the two vehicles were later towed to Londiani Police Station.
The accident caused a traffic gridlock in the area but the scene was later cleared by traffic police officers.
